Class
Description
Admin
The Admin class represents an admin user who can manage the system, such as removing doctors from the list.
AdminTest
This class tests the Admin class and its functionality such as initialization, removing doctors, and showing profile.
Appointment
The Appointment class represents an appointment between a patient and a doctor.
AppointmentSystem
This class implements an appointment system that allows registering patients and doctors, booking appointments, viewing details, and saving data to a file.
AppointmentSystemDAO
This interface defines the methods for managing an appointment system.
AppointmentSystemTest
This class contains unit tests for the AppointmentSystem service class.
AppointmentTest
This class tests the Appointment model class to ensure its methods work correctly.
Doctor
The Doctor class represents a doctor in the system.
DoctorTest
This class tests the Doctor model class to ensure it behaves correctly.
InvalidAppointmentException
This class represents a custom exception for handling invalid appointment-related scenarios.
InvalidAppointmentExceptionTest
This class tests the functionality of the InvalidAppointmentException class.
Main
This is the main user interface class for the Medical Appointment System.
Patient
The Patient class represents a patient in the system.
PatientTest
This class tests the Patient model class.
Security
The Security annotation is used to define role-based access control for a particular class.
User
This is an abstract class that represents a user in the system.
UserTest
This class tests the User abstract class using a concrete inner class called TestUser.
